1. IntelliJ-IDEA 2017.2
	Download Address: https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/download
	Use Ultimate Edition.
	Tips: Using Uwindsor email to active the IDE for student permit.

2. Maven. 
	Pick up one to setup Maven.Apache.
	https://maven.apache.org/guides/getting-started/windows-prerequisites.html
	https://www.mkyong.com/maven/how-to-install-maven-in-windows/
	http://bitbybitblog.com/install-maven-mac/
	https://wilsonmar.github.io/maven-on-macos/
	http://www.jianshu.com/p/191685a33786
	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ghIvOYDs0BM

3. OpenCV
	There are two files in dictionary ‘lib’ that should be included in the project.
		1. opencv-330.jar
		2. libopev_java330.dylib (in OSX) or lib330.dll (in WINDOWS)
	The OpenCV which we used, is version 3.3.0. 
	Here is the link shows how to setup OpenCV3.x on local systems. http://opencv-java-tutorials.readthedocs.io/en/latest/01-installing-opencv-for-java.html#install-opencv-3-x-under-macos

Tips:
As a advice, I recommand to use brew tools for building working environment on OSX.